<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> If the contract of employment or the employment relationship is terminated because the transfer involves a substantial change in working conditions to the detriment of the employee, the employer shall be regarded as having been responsible for termination of the contract of employment or of the employment relationship. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;suhe l&otilde;petatakse sellep&auml;rast, et &uuml;leminek toob kaasa t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste olulise muutuse t&ouml;&ouml;taja kahjuks, loetakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja vastutavaks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;suhte katkestamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4a </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4a </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Unless Member States provide otherwise, Articles 3 and 4 shall not apply to any transfer of an undertaking, business or part of an undertaking or business where the transferor is the subject of bankruptcy proceedings or any analogous insolvency proceedings which have been instituted with a view to the liquidation of the assets of the transferor and are under the supervision of a competent public authority (which may be an insolvency practitioner authorised by a competent public authority). </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid ei n&auml;e ette teisiti, ei kohaldata artikleid 3 ja 4 ettev&otilde;tte, &auml;ri&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu osa &uuml;lemineku suhtes, kui v&otilde;&otilde;randaja vastu on algatatud pankrotimenetlus v&otilde;i analoogiline maksej&otilde;uetusmenetlus v&otilde;&otilde;randaja varade likvideerimiseks, mis toimub p&auml;deva asutuse j&auml;relevalve all (kelleks v&otilde;ib olla p&auml;deva asutuse m&auml;&auml;ratud pankrotihaldur). </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
