<eesti> Kui artikleid 3 ja 4 kohaldatakse maksej&otilde;uetusmenetluse raames toimuva &uuml;lemineku suhtes (s&otilde;ltumata sellest, kas menetlus on algatatud v&otilde;&otilde;randaja varade likvideerimiseks v&otilde;i mitte), tingimusel et menetlus toimub p&auml;deva asutuse j&auml;relevalve all (kelleks v&otilde;ib olla siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ratud pankrotihaldur), v&otilde;ib liikmesriik ette n&auml;ha, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) notwithstanding Article 3(1), the transferor's debts arising from any contracts of employment or employment relationships and payable before the transfer or before the opening of the insolvency proceedings shall not be transferred to the transferee, provided that such proceedings give rise, under the law of that Member State, to protection at least equivalent to that provided for in situations covered by Council Directive 80/987/EEC of 20 October 1980 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the protection of employees in the event of the insolvency of their employer (**); and, or alternatively, that </inglise>
<eesti> a) olenemata artikli 3 l&otilde;ikest 1 ei l&auml;he mis tahes t&ouml;&ouml;lepingust v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;suhtest tulenevad v&otilde;&otilde;randaja v&otilde;lad, mis tuleb v&auml;lja maksta enne &uuml;leminekut v&otilde;i enne maksej&otilde;uetusmenetluse algatamist, &uuml;le omandajale, tingimusel et selline menetlus toob liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kaasa kaitse, mis on v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rdne sellisteks olukordadeks etten&auml;htud kaitsega, mis on s&auml;testatud n&otilde;ukogu 20. oktoobri 1980. aasta direktiivis 80/987/EM&Uuml; t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kaitset nende t&ouml;&ouml;andja maksej&otilde;uetuse puhul k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide seaduste &uuml;htlustamise kohta; ja/v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the transferee, transferor, or person or persons exercising the transferor's functions, on the one hand, and the representatives of the employees on the other hand may agree alterations, insofar as current law or practice permits, to the employees' terms and conditions of employment designed to safeguard employment opportunities by ensuring the survival of the undertaking, business or part of the undertaking or business. </inglise>
<eesti> b) omandaja, v&otilde;&otilde;randaja v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randaja funktsioone t&auml;itev isik v&otilde;i t&auml;itvad isikud &uuml;helt poolt ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajad teiselt poolt v&otilde;ivad kehtiva &otilde;iguse v&otilde;i tava kohaselt lubatud m&auml;&auml;ral otsustada muuta t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imaluste kaitseks t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi, tagades ettev&otilde;tte, &auml;ri&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu tegevuse j&auml;tkumise. </eesti>
