<inglise> The transferor must give such information to the representatives of his employees in good time before the transfer is carried out. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;&otilde;randaja peab sellise teabe esitama oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajatele aegsasti enne &uuml;leminekut. </eesti>
<inglise> The transferee must give such information to the representatives of his employees in good time, and in any event before his employees are directly affected by the transfer as regards their conditions of work and employment. </inglise>
<eesti> Omandaja peab sellise teabe esitama oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajatele aegsasti ning igal juhul enne seda, kui &uuml;leminek tema t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid seoses nende t&ouml;&ouml;- ja t&ouml;&ouml;suhte tingimustega otseselt m&otilde;jutab. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the transferor or the transferee envisages measures in relation to his employees, he shall consult the representatives of his employees in good time on such measures with a view to reaching an agreement. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui v&otilde;&otilde;randaja v&otilde;i omandaja kavandab meetmeid oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes, peab ta alustama t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajatega aegsasti konsultatsioone selliste meetmete suhtes, eesm&auml;rgiga saavutada kokkulepe. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States whose laws, regulations or administrative provisions provide that representatives of the employees may have recourse to an arbitration board to obtain a decision on the measures to be taken in relation to employees may limit the obligations laid down in paragraphs 1 and 2 to cases where the transfer carried out gives rise to a change in the business likely to entail serious disadvantages for a considerable number of the employees. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid, mille &otilde;igus- v&otilde;i haldusnormides s&auml;testatakse, et t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajad v&otilde;ivad p&ouml;&ouml;rduda vahekohtu poole selleks, et saada otsus t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes kavandatavate meetmete kohta, v&otilde;ivad piirata l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 etten&auml;htud kohustusi juhtumitega, kus toimunud &uuml;leminek p&otilde;hjustab &auml;ritegevuses muudatusi, millel on t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt t&otilde;sised olukorda halvendavad tagaj&auml;rjed m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rse arvu t&ouml;&ouml;tajate jaoks. </eesti>
<inglise> The information and consultations shall cover at least the measures envisaged in relation to the employees. </inglise>
<eesti> Teavitamis- ja konsulteerimismenetlus peab k&auml;sitlema v&auml;hemalt meetmeid, mida t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes kavandatakse. </eesti>
<inglise> The information must be provided and consultations taken place in good time before the change in the business as referred to in the first subparagraph is effected. </inglise>
<eesti> Teavitada ja konsulteerida tuleb aegsasti enne &auml;ritegevuses toimuvaid muudatusi, millele on viidatud esimeses l&otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The obligations laid down in this Article shall apply irrespective of whether the decision resulting in the transfer is taken by the employer or an undertaking controlling the employer. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva artikliga etten&auml;htud kohustused kehtivad s&otilde;ltumata sellest, kas &uuml;leminekuni viinud otsuse tegi t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjat kontrolliv ettev&otilde;te. </eesti>
<inglise> In considering alleged breaches of the information and consultation requirements laid down by this Directive, the argument that such a breach occurred because the information was not provided by an undertaking controlling the employer shall not be accepted as an excuse. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiiviga etten&auml;htud teavitamis- ja konsulteerimisn&otilde;uete v&auml;idetava rikkumise puhul ei loeta vabandavaks v&auml;idet, et rikkumise p&otilde;hjuseks on asjaolu, et t&ouml;&ouml;andjat kontrolliv ettev&otilde;te ei andnud teavet. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may limit the obligations laid down in paragraphs 1, 2 and 3 to undertakings or businesses which, in terms of the number of employees, meet the conditions for the election or nomination of a collegiate body representing the employees. </inglise>
